This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic segmentation of high resolution remote sensing imagery using convolutional neural networks. The paper also discusses the use of dilated convolutions, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel architecture for improving semantic segmentation performance. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for remote sensing tasks. 

The graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a possibility as remote sensing imagery is often used in geographic information systems and cartography. 

Finally, the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is a possibility as remote sensing is often used in robotics applications such as autonomous navigation and mapping.
